      <h1 class='title'>Social Security Benefits Uprating 2004</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 11 December 2003 vol 415 cc106-16WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_106ws' title='Col. 106WS &mdash; HC Deb 11 December 2003 vol 415 c106WS' name='column_106ws' href='#column_106ws' rel='bookmark'>106WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0415P2_20031211_CWS_14'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-andrew-smith' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0415P2_20031211_CWS_14' title='Link to this speech by Mr Andrew Smith' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-andrew-smith" title="Mr Andrew Smith">The Secretary of State for Work and Pensions (Mr. Andrew Smith)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The proposed rates of benefit for 2004 are set out in the table below. The annual uprating of benefits will take place for State Pension and most other benefits in the first full week of the tax year. In 2004, this will be the week beginning 12 April. My right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland proposes to introduce similar changes for Northern Ireland.</p><p>
